name: ImpairedFetalGrowthI9
title: Impaired Fetal Growth I9
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains diagnosis most commonly used for newborns with impaired fetal growth.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify newborns who have an active  diagnosis of impaired fetal growth. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the "Diagnosis" category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Codes representing the ICD-9 code system for the diagnosis of impaired fetal growth.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that do not meet inclusion criteria.)
